sec.p:
The following criteria led to exclusion of a patient:
smoking >15 cigarettes per day;
known or suspected non‐compliance, drug or alcohol abuse;
inability to follow study procedures, for example, due to language problems, psychological disorders, dementia, etc.;
poor oral hygiene (plaque control record > 30%);
pregnancy at the date of inclusion.

Following abutment connection and before taking the impression for the final crown, patients were randomly allocated to one of three groups by using a sealed envelope containing the group allocation according to a computer‐generated list:
CONVEX (customization of an undercontoured provisional screw‐retained crown to a convex contour) (n = 15);
CONCAVE (customization of an undercontoured provisional screw‐retained crown to a concave contour) (n = 16);
CONTROL (no customization by using a standardized healing abutment): No provisional restoration; however, the use of larger diameter healing abutment was allowed when deemed necessary (n = 16).
